name: Valerian cubes, Valerian toy, toy for cats, plush cubes, gift, cat toy, Crazy Cat Lady, unique
description: Each cube of valerian measures about 4x4x4cm, is made of cotton and filled with polyester OR organic quality spelt husk and 3g ground valerian root.Spelt husk is a pure natural product and seduces with its light crackling sound to wild romping and playing.If you want, you can pimp the toy for the tiger with a bell or crackling foil.In addition, each cube is a unique toy for your cat.Individually airtight welded. If you buy several valerian toys, they are sealed together to avoid unnecessary packaging waste.If you buy a toy, a cube will be sent by chance. You can also leave a color of your choice in the comment. We will then choose an appropriate cube. IMPORTANT! Valerian and toys with it should only be given under supervision. Also not more than 1-2 times a week - otherwise cats get used to the smell and lose interest.It is best to keep it outside the playing time in an airtight bag (or wrap well with cling film), so that the scent is preserved for a long time.Colors may vary depending on the device.

name: Mouth protection mask, makeshift mask, makeshift face mask, nose protection, face mask, everyday mask, elastic band, washable
description: Simple and reusable makeshift mask for everyday use.Made entirely of cotton, with elastic bands for wearing and opening for a filter.There are different possibilities for cleaning:Cooking potIf you don't want to start a machine for one or more masks, you can also boil the mask for at least five minutes in a saucepan with water and a pinch of detergent. This is the quick method, so to speak. To determine the correct temperature, you can use a kitchen or grill thermometer. Once the masks are boiled, you should let them dry well.KettlePour hot water from the kettle at a temperature of at least 70 °C into a pot or heat-resistant bowl. Put the mask in for five minutes, stirring it from time to time with a wooden spoon. Then take it out, lay it out on a towel and let it dry well.These masks are neither a medical product nor protective equipment.Proper handling is therefore important and is strongly recommended.Colors may vary depending on the device.

name: Dirted wood bowl
description: Beautiful hand turned bowl of thermo Spruce, with a really great grain.The shell consists of several rings that were individually glued and then ground together.The wooden bowl was hooked with a wooden balm consisting of orange oil and beeswax, so everything naturally and without chemistry.The different grains of the individual rings result in a unique look.The used thermo Spruce is a native wood, which is by a thermal treatment, exposure to high heat, significantly more resistant to moisture and fungi.Therefore also ideal as a fruit bowl or as a bowl for nibbles.Usually thermo Spruce is used for terrace planks because it is so durable.For the care of the wooden bowl it is enough to rub them regularly with a little olives or other oil e.g. orange oil and to polish something.Diameter: About 25 cmHeight: ca 12 cmWeight: 252gHave fun fillingBy the way, the TV and decoration are not included in the price;))

name: handmade wooden ring with blue Resin inlay
description: Wooden ring, handmade wooden ring with blue Resin inlay, wood metal ring, wooden rings, wooden engagement ring, wooden jewelry, wedding rings woodWooden ring, handmade with blue resin inlay.This ring of wood and metal was made of a Banksia cone and blue epoxy resin.Our wooden jewelry is made by hand and with love.The wooden ring sits on a ring made of stainless steel, which gives the actual ring of wood a lot of stability and longevity.Due to the individual grain of the individual woods real unique pieces that really only exist once.Each of our wooden rings is made in Germany.The ring box is included in the price.Here are some more information:Ring size:Inner circumference: 2,20472 inchInner diameter: 0,708661 inchRing size EU: 16.5USA, Canada: 7.5England, UK: qRing width: 0,374016 inchThe wood used in this case is a Banksia cones. A Banksia cones is the wooden seedling of a Bankisa tree that grows in Australia. When the seeds have fallen out of the cone, spread the holes over which the seeds have grown over the whole cone, and then can be filled with synthetic resin.This creates, to the already intrinsically interesting grain of the pin still a very interesting color game.The silver ring band is made of stainless steel. The ring was varnished with a boat varnish based on wood oils, which gives the ring a special stability, is water-resistant and scratch-resistant. The paint is suitable for children's toys and therefore safe to wear on the skin, it also gives the wood a beautiful glossy effect.Care instructions: the paint is slightly sensitive to alcohol, so wipe the best if something should come on it. Also when rinsing you should take off the ring in the best case. Otherwise for polishing just take a microfiber cloth and some cooking oil and rub very gently;)) then it shines again like a baby's bottom.Have fun buying and runningyour Rotholz team

Allow differences in heightTermsGeneral Terms and Conditions of Resin Artattack1 Applicability to entrepreneurs and definitions of terms(1) The following General Terms and Conditions apply to all deliveries between us and a consumer in their version valid at the time of ordering.The consumer is any natural person who concludes a legal transaction for purposes that cannot be attributed primarily to his commercial or independent professional activity (Section 13 of the German Civil Code).2 Conclusion of a contract, storage of the contract text(1) The following terms and conditions for the conclusion of the contract apply to orders placed through my Etsy Shophttps://www.etsy.com/de/shop/ResinArtattack(2) In the event of the conclusion of the contract, the contract shall be concluded withResin Artattackachieved.(3) The presentation of the goods in my internet shop does not constitute a legally binding contract offer on my part, but is only a non-binding request to the consumer to order goods. By ordering the desired goods, the consumer makes a binding offer for him to conclude a purchase contract.The acceptance of the offer shall be made in writing or in text form or by sending the ordered goods within three weeks. After fruitless expiry of the period, the offer is deemed to have been rejected.(4) Upon receipt of an order in my internet shop, the following regulations apply: The consumer makes a binding contract offer by successfully going through the order procedure provided for in my internet shop.The order is made in the following steps:1) Selection of the desired goods2) Confirm by clicking on the "Order" buttons3) Checking the information in the shopping cart4) Actuation of the button "to the checkout"5) Registration in the Internet shop after registration and entering the applicant information (e-mail address and password).6) Re-examination or correction of the respective entered data.7) Binding dispatch of the order by clicking on the button "Order for a fee" or "buy"Before submitting the order in a binding manner, the consumer can return to the website, where the customer's details are recorded and correct input errors or cancel the ordering process by closing the internet browser.(5) Storage of the contract text for orders via my internet shop : I save the contract text. You can find the agb in any offer as well as in my info box.3 Prices, shipping costs, payment, due date(1) The prices quoted include other price components. In addition, there are possible shipping costs.(2) The consumer has the possibility to use all payments accepted by Etsy as in advance, PayPal.(3) If the consumer has chosen the payment in advance, he undertakes to pay the purchase price immediately after the conclusion of the contract.4 Delivery(1) Unless I have clearly stated this in the product description, all offered items will only be made after the order has been received. Delivery is made according to the information in the respective item description. In the case of payment in advance, the deadline for delivery begins to run on the day after the payment order to the bank responsible for the transfer and for all other payment methods on the day after the conclusion of the contract. If the deadline falls on a Saturday, Sunday or public holiday at the place of delivery, the deadline ends on the next working day.(2) The risk of accidental loss and accidental deterioration of the sold item shall not pass to the buyer until the goods are handed over to the buyer, even when the goods are purchased.Section 5 Retention of titleWe reserve ownership of the goods until full payment of the purchase price.Section 6 WarrantyThe statutory warranty regulations apply.Section 7 Contract Language8 Exchange & ReturnAccording to the concrete wording of Section 312 g (2) No. 1 of the German Civil Code (BGB), the statutory right of withdrawal does not exist in the case of contractsfor the supply of goods which are not prefabricated and for the manufacture of which an individual choice or destination by the consumer is decisive or which are clearly tailored to the personal needs of the consumer.Only German is available as the contract language.Status of the General Terms and Conditions Nov.2020Look forward to your visit
